DDL : DATA DEFINITION LANGUAGE
IMPLEMENTING BASIC SQL COMMANDS
1.CREATE : TO CREATE TABLES, PROCEDURES, TRIGGERS ETC
2.ALTER : TO MODIFY THE STRUCTURE OF TABLE 
3.TRUNCATE : TO DELETE ALL THE DATA, BUT NOT THE TABLE
4.DROP : ENTIRE TABLE WILL BE DELETED, ALSO DATA
5.RENAME : RENAME TABLES, COLUMNS IN DBMS
Example : Alter table St_info Rename to St_information
for columns : Alter table St_information Rename m1 to physics 
NOTE : This is auto commit language.(everything will be saved.)

DML : DATA MANIPULATION LANGUAGE
IMPLEMENTING BASIC SQL COMMANDS
1.INSERT COMMAND : TO INSERT DATA INTO THE TABLE
2.UPDATE : TO UPDATE THE COLUMNS (USE SET WITH IT)

19th jan codes:
create table student_info (prn INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), m1 INT, m2 INT, m3 INT);
1.select * from tab; (to see no of tables in database)
2.desc student_info #student_info(to see the attributes in the table or table structure)
3.Insert data in table 
insert into student_info (101,'xyz', 65, 75, 85); #error : missing select keyword
insert into student_info values (101,'xyz', 65, 75, 85);
1 row created.
insert into student_info values (102,'abc', 5, 6, 7);
4. add column to st_info:
alter table student_info add total number;
alter table student_info dd perc number;
